    #<Burst-Fire Rockets>

        #<Description>

            By Aaron0000

            Replaces the accuracy accessory of Rocket Launchers. Changes it to give rocket launchers a 3-round burst fire at the cost of reduced damage and accuracy.

            Comes with custom prefixes: Maliwan = Resurging, Tediore = Repeating, Torgue = Triple Entendre, Bandit = bang bang, Vladof = Troynoy.

            Atlas Reborn also has an optional prefix located at the bottom. Activate this file after Atlas Reborn to enable the prefix properly.

        #</Description>

        #<Code>

            set GD_Weap_Launchers.Accessory.RL_Accessory_BodyMod_2_Acc WeaponAttributeEffects ((AttributeToModify=AttributeDefinition'D_Attributes.Weapon.WeaponFireInterval',ModifierType=MT_PreAdd,BaseModifierValue=(BaseValueConstant=1.000000,BaseValueAttribute=None,InitializationDefinition=None,BaseValueScaleConstant=0.500000)),(AttributeToModify=AttributeDefinition'D_Attributes.Weapon.WeaponFireInterval',ModifierType=MT_Scale,BaseModifierValue=(BaseValueConstant=-0.7500000,BaseValueAttribute=None,InitializationDefinition=None,BaseValueScaleConstant=10.000000)),(AttributeToModify=AttributeDefinition'D_Attributes.Weapon.WeaponAutomaticBurstCount',ModifierType=MT_PreAdd,BaseModifierValue=(BaseValueConstant=1.000000,BaseValueAttribute=None,InitializationDefinition=None,BaseValueScaleConstant=3.000000)),(AttributeToModify=AttributeDefinition'D_Attributes.Weapon.WeaponDamage',ModifierType=MT_Scale,BaseModifierValue=(BaseValueConstant=-0.700000,BaseValueAttribute=None,InitializationDefinition=None,BaseValueScaleConstant=1.000000)),(AttributeToModify=AttributeDefinition'D_Attributes.Weapon.WeaponBurstInterval',ModifierType=MT_Scale,BaseModifierValue=(BaseValueConstant=1.000000,BaseValueAttribute=None,InitializationDefinition=None,BaseValueScaleConstant=-0.500000)),(AttributeToModify=AttributeDefinition'D_Attributes.Weapon.WeaponSpread',ModifierType=MT_Scale,BaseModifierValue=(BaseValueConstant=1.000000,BaseValueAttribute=None,InitializationDefinition=None,BaseValueScaleConstant=1.500000)))

            set GD_Weap_Launchers.Name.Prefix_Bandit.Prefix_BodyMod2_Accuracy PartName bang bang

            set GD_Weap_Launchers.Name.Prefix_Maliwan.Prefix_BodyMod2_Accuracy PartName Resurging

            set GD_Weap_Launchers.Name.Prefix_Tediore.Prefix_BodyMod2_Accuracy PartName Repeating

            set GD_Weap_Launchers.Name.Prefix_Torgue.Prefix_BodyMod2_Accuracy PartName Triple Entendre

            set GD_Weap_Launchers.Name.Prefix_Vladof.Prefix_BodyMod2_Accuracy PartName Troynoy

        #</Code>

        #<Atlas Prefix>

            set GD_Weap_Launchers.Name.Prefix_Vladof.Prefix_BodyMod2_Accuracy PartName Extreme

        #</Atlas Prefix>

    #</Burst-Fire Rockets>

    #<Classic Sledge's Shotgun>

        #<Description>

            By Aaron0000

            Turns Sledge's Shotgun into a recreation of his weapon from Borderlands 1.

            Features;

            Increased base damage.

            -1 projectile

            +15% multiplicative critical damage

            +10000% Burst Fire

            +100% Melee Damage (But 150% with the melee attachment)

            Decreased reload speed

            2-shot magazine regardless of variants; consumes one ammo per shot

            Always spawns with a Bayonet (but does not erase non-bayonet variants).

            Knockback returns!

            Two options for skins. Red skin is on by default.

            NOTE:

            If using S&S Forever, there is a compatibility version at the bottom. Activate this version after S&S Forever if you would rather use this weapon instead of the S&S "Perseids".

            If using the Quadtastic mod, there is a compatibility fix for it located at the bottom.

            If using both S&S and Quadtastic, there is a combined fix at the bottom.

            If using S&S Lite, simply use the normal version and activate it after S&S. Use the Quadtastic version if using Quadtastic Sledge's Shotgun.

        #</Description>

        #<Code>

            set GD_Weap_Shotgun.Barrel.SG_Barrel_Jakobs_Sledges GestaltModeSkeletalMeshName SG_Barrel_Jakobs

            set GD_Weap_Shotgun.A_Weapons_Legendary.SG_Bandit_5_SledgesShotgun:WeaponPartListCollectionDefinition_135 Accessory1PartData (bEnabled=True,WeightedParts=((bDisabled=False,Part=WeaponPartDefinition'GD_Weap_Shotgun.Accessory.SG_Accessory_Bayonet_2',Manufacturers=,MinGameStageIndex=0,MaxGameStageIndex=1,DefaultWeightIndex=0),(bDisabled=False,Part=WeaponPartDefinition'GD_Weap_Shotgun.Accessory.SG_Accessory_MoonClip',Manufacturers=,MinGameStageIndex=0,MaxGameStageIndex=0,DefaultWeightIndex=0),(bDisabled=False,Part=WeaponPartDefinition'GD_Weap_Shotgun.Accessory.SG_Accessory_ShotgunShell',Manufacturers=,MinGameStageIndex=0,MaxGameStageIndex=0,DefaultWeightIndex=0),(bDisabled=False,Part=WeaponPartDefinition'GD_Weap_Shotgun.Accessory.SG_Accessory_Tech_1',Manufacturers=,MinGameStageIndex=0,MaxGameStageIndex=0,DefaultWeightIndex=0),(bDisabled=False,Part=WeaponPartDefinition'GD_Weap_Shotgun.Accessory.SG_Accessory_Tech_2',Manufacturers=,MinGameStageIndex=0,MaxGameStageIndex=0,DefaultWeightIndex=0),(bDisabled=False,Part=WeaponPartDefinition'GD_Weap_Shotgun.Accessory.SG_Accessory_Tech_3',Manufacturers=,MinGameStageIndex=0,MaxGameStageIndex=0,DefaultWeightIndex=0),(bDisabled=False,Part=WeaponPartDefinition'GD_Weap_Shotgun.Accessory.SG_Accessory_VerticalGrip',Manufacturers=,MinGameStageIndex=0,MaxGameStageIndex=0,DefaultWeightIndex=0)))

            set GD_Weap_Shotgun.Barrel.SG_Barrel_Jakobs_Sledges WeaponAttributeEffects ((AttributeToModify=AttributeDefinition'D_Attributes.Weapon.WeaponShotCost',ModifierType=MT_PreAdd,BaseModifierValue=(BaseValueConstant=0.500000,BaseValueAttribute=None,InitializationDefinition=None,BaseValueScaleConstant=1.000000)),(AttributeToModify=AttributeDefinition'D_Attributes.Weapon.WeaponProjectilesPerShot',ModifierType=MT_PreAdd,BaseModifierValue=(BaseValueConstant=1.000000,BaseValueAttribute=None,InitializationDefinition=None,BaseValueScaleConstant=5.000000)),(AttributeToModify=AttributeDefinition'D_Attributes.Weapon.WeaponClipSize',ModifierType=MT_Scale,BaseModifierValue=(BaseValueConstant=-99999.000000,BaseValueAttribute=None,InitializationDefinition=None,BaseValueScaleConstant=1.000000)),(AttributeToModify=AttributeDefinition'D_Attributes.Weapon.WeaponClipSize',ModifierType=MT_PostAdd,BaseModifierValue=(BaseValueConstant=2.000000,BaseValueAttribute=None,InitializationDefinition=None,BaseValueScaleConstant=1.000000)),(AttributeToModify=AttributeDefinition'D_Attributes.Weapon.WeaponAutomaticBurstCount',ModifierType=MT_PreAdd,BaseModifierValue=(BaseValueConstant=100.000000,BaseValueAttribute=None,InitializationDefinition=None,BaseValueScaleConstant=1.000000)),(AttributeToModify=AttributeDefinition'D_Attributes.Weapon.WeaponDamage',ModifierType=MT_Scale,BaseModifierValue=(BaseValueConstant=0.511000,BaseValueAttribute=None,InitializationDefinition=None,BaseValueScaleConstant=1.000000)),(AttributeToModify=AttributeDefinition'D_Attributes.Weapon.WeaponKnockback',ModifierType=MT_PreAdd,BaseModifierValue=(BaseValueConstant=1.000000,BaseValueAttribute=None,InitializationDefinition=None,BaseValueScaleConstant=1.000000)),(AttributeToModify=AttributeDefinition'D_Attributes.Weapon.WeaponKnockback',ModifierType=MT_Scale,BaseModifierValue=(BaseValueConstant=45.500000,BaseValueAttribute=None,InitializationDefinition=None,BaseValueScaleConstant=1.000000)),(AttributeToModify=AttributeDefinition'D_Attributes.Weapon.WeaponFireInterval',ModifierType=MT_Scale,BaseModifierVal     #<Fast Talker>

        #<Description>

            By Aaron0000

            Replaces the Bone Shredder with the Fast Talker from Pre-Sequel.

            Features;

            High fire rate and quick reload speed for a Bandit submachine gun.

            Increased accuracy.

            NOTE:

            If using S&S Forever, there is a compatibility version at the bottom. Activate this version after S&S Forever if you want to use this weapon instead of the S&S "Polaris".

            If using S&S Lite, simply activate this file (do not use the S&S Forever fix) after S&S Lite if you'd rather use the Fast Talker instead of Polaris.

        #</Description>

    #</Legendary Monk>

    #<Atlas Reborn>

        #<Description>

            By Aaron0000

            Atlas Reborn

            Completely overhauls the Vladof manufacturer into Atlas from Borderlands 1.

            #<List of changes>

                All Vladof items (excluding class mods and some unique/seraph items) have been reskinned and renamed. This includes gemstone skins (now Orichalcum) and prefixes. Names are based off of Greek weapons and prefixes are based off of "superiority" as well as a few BL1 prefixes (List of Prefixes and Titles can be found below).

                Atlas Weapons have been globally rebalanced. The stats should be above average in all aspects.

                Most special weapons have been replaced or adjusted. Details down below.

                Atlas weapons have the feature of increasing action skill cooldown while held.

            #</List of changes>

            #<Notes>

                Already encorporates the GemstoneFixes mod for Vladof weapons.

                If using the community patch, load this file after the community patch. In general, load this file last.

                Chimera uses the splashes/explosions of the Twister and Hornet to achieve the desired effect. If a mod alters those splashes, it will affect the Chimera.

                #<Reticle>

                    If you're having issues with reticles disappearing, it is a known issue. Due to gearbox wizardry, depending on the grip of a weapon, and the barrel of said weapon, the scoped view will have missing parts when using the Atlas logo. Find this line in the file:

                    GD_Manufacturers.Manufacturers.Vladof FlashLabelName Atlas

                    and disable it or use FilterTool.

                #</Reticle>

            #</Notes>

            #<Replacers & Renamings>

                #<Replacers>

                    Infinity -> Chimera

                    Shredifier -> Griffin

                    Lyuda -> Cyclops

                    Mongol -> Hydra

                    Stinger -> Troll

                    Patriot -> Argus

                    Lead Storm -> Ogre

                    Stalker -> Aries

                    Rapier -> Ajax's Spear

                    Veritas -> Erinyes

                    Aequitas -> Shield of Heracles

                    #<Details>

                        #<Chimera>

                            Always spawns in Fire versions (Does not remove other versions, but using non-Fire versions is not advised).

                            Has Shock and Corrosive splash damage.

                            Consumes two ammo per shot.

                        #</Chimera>

                        #<Griffon>

                            Boosted base stats (Damage, accuracy, fire rate, magazine size, reload speed, recoil).

                            Further boosted Action Skill cooldown.

                            Increased projectile speed.

                            Only spawns in elemental versions.

                        #</Griffon>

                        #<Cyclops>

                            Always spawns with a Hyperion scope.

                            Increased Critical Hit Damage.

                            x11.2 Zoom.

                            +30% damage.

                            Reduced minimum spread.

                            Increased accuracy when scoped.

                            Doubled projectile speed.

                            Produces transfusion orbs upon hitting an enemy.

                        #</Cyclops>

                        #<Hydra>

                            Fires five rockets in a horizontal spread.

                            Actually does consume reduced ammo.

                            Decreased damage per projectile.

                            Increased accuracy.

                        #</Hydra>

                        #<Troll>

                            Minor stat boosts.

                            Increases damage resistance to all types while wielded (except fire).

                            Grants health regeneration while held.

                        #</Troll>

                        #<Argus>

                            Behaves like a shotgun when hip-fired, and like a sniper rifle when aiming down sights.

                            Decreased critical hit damage when hip-fired, increased critical damage when aiming down sights.

                            Extended magazine capacity.

                        #</Argus>

                        #<Ogre>

                            Deals explosive damage regardless of element (Does not remove elemental versions, but always deals non-elemental damage on the bullet regardless. Using elemental versions will just lower the damage).

                            Increased base damage.

                            Significantly reduced spread.

                            Heavily reduced recoil.

                            Has a unique spread pattern.

                        #</Ogre>

                        #<Aries>

                            Always spawns in shock (Does not remove non-shock versions that already exist, however.)

                            Heavily boosted damage.

                            Heavily reduced fire rate.

                            Decreased spread.

                            +100 Critical hit damage.

                            Shooting an enemy will produce transfusion trails.

                        #</Aries>

                        #<Ajax's Spear>

                            Still has the same Melee effects as the Rapier. Just made it more effective as an actual gun.

                            Increased base damage.

                            Significantly reduced spread.

                            Heavily reduced recoil.

                        #</Ajax's Spear>

                        #<Erinyes>

                            60% increased fire rate.

                            Burst-fires the entire magazine when the trigger is pulled.

                            No bullet spread.

                            Reduced damage.

                            Longer reload times.

                            No longer has the Aequitas-partner effect.

                        #</Erinyes>

                        #<Shield of Heracles>

                            Absorption shield with 50% elemental adapation resistance.

                            No longer has the Veritas-partner effect.

                        #</Shield of Heracles>

                    #</Details>

                #</Replacers>

                #<Renamings>

                    Sham -> Aegis

                    Transformer -> Omega

                    Sponge -> Leo

                    Fire Bee -> Phoenix

                    Storm Front -> Steropes

                    Pandemic -> Python

                #</Renamings>

                #<Adjustments>

                    #<Kitten>

                        Gave Kitten a new, tighter spread and reduced the damage slightly to compensate.

                    #</Kitten>

                    #<Hail>

                        Cut the arc of Hail in half.

                    #</Hail>

                #</Adjustments>

            #</Replacers & Renamings>

            #<Prefixes>

                Atlas Prefix ------------- Prefix type -------------------------- Vladof Prefix

                #<Shared>

                    Noteworthy -------------- Bandit grip --------------------------- Forlorn

                    High-Caliber ------------ Jakobs grip --------------------------- Oppressed/Sladky

                    Impressive -------------- Torgue grip --------------------------- Grim

                    Solid ------------------- Dahl grip ----------------------------- Woeful/Nochy

                    Pearl ------------------- Vladof grip --------------------------- Angry/Kot

                    Implacable -------------- Hyperion grip ------------------------- Despair/Sneety

                    Consistent -------------- Tediore grip -------------------------- Icy

                    Orichalcum -------------- Gemstone ------------------------------ Garnet

                #</Shared>

                #<Assault Rifles>

                    Siege ------------------- Basic --------------------------------- Assault

                    Optimal ----------------- BanditClamp (Damage) ------------------ Ferocious

                    Supreme ----------------- BanditClamp (Wild) -------------------- Rabid

                    Impaling ---------------- Bayonet ------------------------------- Skewering

                    Surpassing -------------- Box BulletSpeed ----------------------- Swift

                    Prevailing -------------- Stability Foregrip -------------------- Resolute

                    Maximal ----------------- Magazine Size ------------------------- Expansive

                    Distinguishing ---------- Accuracy ------------------------------ Severe

                    Flaming ----------------- Incendiary ---------------------------- Hot

                    Static ------------------ Shock --------------------------------- Sapping

                    Caustic ----------------- Corrosive ----------------------------- Corrosive

                    Disseminating ----------- Slag ---------------------------------- Slag

                #</Assault Rifles>

                #<Sniper Rifles>

                    Superb ------------------ Damage -------------------------------- Gromky

                    Bisecting --------------- Bayonet ------------------------------- Britva

                    Choice ------------------ Accurate ------------------------------ Zammechat

                    Expert ------------------ Critical ------------------------------ Razrez

                    Steadfast --------------- Stability ----------------------------- Dobby

                    Exceeding --------------- Magazine ------------------------------ Bolshy

                    Incredible -------------- Fire Rate ----------------------------- Skorry

                    Burning ----------------- Incendiary ---------------------------- Phospher

                    Vitrolic ---------------- Corrosive ----------------------------- Splodge

                #</Sniper Rifles>

                #<Pistols>

                    Prime ------------------- Tech 2 (Damage) -----------------------

                    Immeasurable ------------ Fire rate ----------------------------- Vengeful

                    Untold ------------------ Double -------------------------------- Dva

                    Incendiary -------------- Incendiary ---------------------------- Burning

                    Shock ------------------- Shock --------------------------------- Discharge

                    Corrosive --------------- Corrosive ----------------------------- Caustic

                    Slagging ---------------- Slag ---------------------------------- Slag

                #</Pistols>

                #<Rocket Launchers>

                    Grand ------------------- Tip Cover (Damage) -------------------- Rugged

                    Scrupulous -------------- Body Mod 2 (Accuracy) ----------------- Victorious

                    Uninteruptable ---------- Gripper (Reload) ---------------------- Ruthless

                    Mercurial --------------- Handle (Swap Speed) ------------------- Moscovite's

                    Velocious --------------- Stock Cover (Speed) ------------------- Partisan

                    Insurpassable ----------- Stocktube (Fire Rate) ----------------- Turbulent

                    Unrelenting ------------- Body Mod 1 (Mag Size) ----------------- Worker's

                    Cleaving ---------------- Bandit Grip (Melee) ------------------- Revolt

                    Combustion -------------- Incendiary ---------------------------- Red

                    Fulgragating ------------ Shock --------------------------------- Shock

                    Pestilent --------------- Corrosive ----------------------------- Virulent

                    Corrupting -------------- Slag ---------------------------------- Opposing

                #</Rocket Launchers>

                #<Shields>

                    Ace --------------------- Basic --------------------------------- Socialized

                    Indivisble -------------- Capacity 1 ---------------------------- Traitorous

                    Indomitable ------------- Capacity 2 ---------------------------- Meek

                    Indestructable ---------- Capacity 3 ---------------------------- Righteous

                    Impenetrable ------------ Capacity 4 ---------------------------- Unyielding

                    Invincible -------------- Capacity 5 ---------------------------- Unbroken

                    Cut-Above --------------- Rate 1 -------------------------------- Cowardly

                    High-Class -------------- Rate 2 -------------------------------- Timid

                    Five-Star --------------- Rate 3 -------------------------------- Momentous

                    Unrivaled --------------- Rate 4 -------------------------------- Mobilized

                    Alacritous -------------- Rate 5 -------------------------------- Revolutionary

                    Centisecond ------------- Delay 1 ------------------------------- Apathetic

                    Millisecond ------------- Delay 2 ------------------------------- Torpid

                    Microsecond ------------- Delay 3 ------------------------------- Ever-Alert

                    Nanosecond -------------- Delay 4 ------------------------------- Vigilant

                    Immediate --------------- Delay 5 ------------------------------- Watchful

                    Good -------------------- Special 1 ----------------------------- Oppressive

                    Admirable --------------- Special 2 ----------------------------- Restrictive

                    Remarkable -------------- Special 3 ----------------------------- Guerilla

                    Exceptional ------------- Special 4 ----------------------------- Liberated

                    The Best ---------------- Special 5 ----------------------------- Proud

                #</Shields>

            #</Prefixes>

            #<Titles>

                Atlas Title ------------- Item type ----------------------------- Vladof Item Replaced

                Rifle ------------------- Standard assault rifles --------------- Rifle

                Xyston ------------------ Minigun barrel assault rifle ----------

        #</Description>

    #<Cryo Beta>

        #<Cryo Element>

            #<Description>

                By Aaron0000, Kazy, Mike, FromDarkHell, and The Campin' Dutchman.

                Turns Slag into a facsimile of the Pre-Sequel Cryo element.

                Features;

                +125% movement slowdown.

                +250% melee damage.

                +200% explosive damage.

                +200% extra critical hit damage.

                White glows on items that use cryo.

                Slows enemies down when frozen. (Or stops movement completely, if you use the alternative version.)

                Reduces fire rate by 50% when frozen.

                Damage over time.

                Recolored damage numbers.

                Adjusted prefixes/names.

                Reskins for the Grog Nozzle and Slagga (which was renamed to Freeza). Off by default.

                It also includes Pre-Sequel weapon replacers for the following (all of which are off by default);

                Chulainn - Frostfire

                Pyrophobia - Cryophobia

                Fastball - Snowball (but still able to spawn in the other elements)

                Gub - Zim

                Lascaux - Fridgia

                Credits;

                Aaron for the basic functions/attributes, the Pre-Sequel item ports, the reskins, and prefix/title name changes.

                Kazy for making some text changes, the damage number color, and part of the item glows.

                Mike for most of the gfx visual stuff and some other visual bits.

                FromDarkHell for the "freezing" of movement speed option.

                The Campin' Dutchman for advice and coaching.

                Notes;

                If you get stuck in a pool of slag while using the version that stops movement, just spam jump and you should eventually get out.

                There is an option to switch the complete stopping of movement with a heavily reduced movement speed instead.

                (IGNORE THIS FOR NOW) This file contains a hotfix to change the purple "slag" text to a cyan "cryo" text. Be sure to either merge this file with your main file containing hotfixes, or disable the hotfix.

            #</Description>

            #<Code>
